[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-15T16:51:06+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24836298/pikachu_artwork.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">A massive <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/465710/pokemon-game-freak-leak-hack\">leak of data from Pok\u00e9mon developer Game Freak</a>, widely distributed online as the result of a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/analysis/465967/pokemon-game-freak-nintendo-hack-leak\">hack of the company</a>, has revealed new details about the past and future of franchise games, animated series, and live-action projects. That includes unconfirmed intel about the next generation of Pok\u00e9mon \u2014\u00a0aka Gen 10 \u2014\u00a0and a new Pok\u00e9mon game reportedly codenamed <em>Gaia</em>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Few details about the next mainline Pok\u00e9mon game hav", "id": 1330905, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/465913/pokemon-gen-10-gaia-nintendo-switch-2", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The next gen of Pok\u00e9mon may be coming to Switch 2 \u2014\u00a0and the OG Switch", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-15T16:35:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25560945/Helldivers_2_Freedom_s_Flame_2.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Helldivers 2</em> developer Arrowhead Game Studios has been continually tweaking the horde shooter since launch, and some of those changes have been better received than others. After many nerfs to popular weapons and stratagems made the community unhappy, Arrowhead reversed course with a 60-day plan. <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/impressions/455664/helldivers-2-patch-nerf-buff-fix\">The first patch released in September to great acclaim</a>, and now a second round of buffs is arriving with Tuesday\u2019s new patch.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The full patch notes are available on <em>Helldivers 2</em>\u2019", "id": 1330906, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/465978/helldivers-2-buff-patch-throwables-plasma-tank-mines", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Helldivers 2 developer rolls out even more buffs in second big patch", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-15T16:24:55+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: OLM/The Pok\u00e9mon Company\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/18288482/chrome_2019_07_08_14_17_05.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,75.602471042746\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Over the weekend, Pok\u00e9mon source code, art, and other documentation quickly spread across social media and other internet forums. Where did it come from? Game Freak <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/465710/pokemon-game-freak-leak-hack\">confirmed last week</a> it had been hacked, with more than 2,600 pieces of employee data taken. It <em>didn\u2019t</em> confirm the massive heist of its game data, though, but the game data likely originates from that same breach. A hacker alleged they\u2019d acquired 1 TB of data, including source code for <em>Pok\u00e9mon Legends: Z-A</em> and t", "id": 1330907, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/analysis/465967/pokemon-game-freak-nintendo-hack-leak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How do video game companies like Game Freak keep getting hacked?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-15T15:37:32+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Cineverse Entertainment\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/SantaArt.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It\u2019s no surprise that the holiday weekend\u2019s box office returns were dominated by a clown, it\u2019s just probably not the one you expected. After<em> <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/movies/460843/joker-2-review-folie-a-deux\">Joker: Folie \u00e0 Deux</a></em> went from a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/461731/joker-2-box-office-flop-bad\">disappointing opening</a> to one of the <a href=\"https://variety.com/2024/film/box-office/terrifier-3-tops-box-office-joker-folie-a-deux-collapses-1236176346/\">steepest box office declines of any superhero movie ever</a>, the void at the top of the charts was filled by <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/horror/4", "id": 1330562, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/465872/terrifier-3-box-office-total-hit-joker-2-bomb", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Terrifier 3 turns the franchise from a cult favorite into a true box office hit", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-15T15:08:57+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Billy\u2019s face illuminates a TV in Fortnite\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Epic Games via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/fortnite-fortnitemares-billy-face.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Billy the Puppet</strong> from the Saw franchise is in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/fortnite-battle-royale/40155\">Fortnite</a></em> as a boss with the arrival of this year\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/fortnite-guide/464115/fortnitemares-event-start-date-time-est-pst-bst\">Fortnitemares</a> event. And one of the Fortnitemares quests is to find and defeat him.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>Fortnite</em> Fortnitemares guide will tell you where to find Billy the Puppet, how to summon him, and how to defeat him to complete the <strong>find